  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Littoral Integrated Pig Farming Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Farmers</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This umbrella project will assist 450 resource-limited farm families of the Littoral region (Mungo and Sanaga maritime) and Santchou in Menoua Division. A total of 3,600 pigs will be distributed over the course of the project, with family receiving eight pigs. At least 60 percent of project participants will be women and disadvantaged persons. Ninety original families will receive 720 animals, and during the course of the project 2,880 animals will be passed on to another 360 families. Families will also receive hands-on training in animal and crop husbandry, crop and animal preservation and transformation, integration of crop-livestock techniques, gardening and Heifer&#x2019;s 12 Cornerstones, among others. They will receive agricultural equipment and supplies, and horticulture inputs to enable them build up production assets. The project will also address HIV and AIDS, gender equity and environmental issues.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&quot;Hands-on training of farmers in animal and crop husbandry, crop and animal preservation and transformation, integration of crop-livestock techniques, market gardening, Heifer&#x2019;s 12 cornerstones for just and sustainable development, group development and management, resource mobilization and management. Facilitate access to related agricultural equipment/supplies, and horticulture inputs - Sensitize on HIV and AIDS, gender equity and environmental issues.&quot;</narrative>
  </description>
